reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Be careful where you use these
reviews.reviewText: In general, the cables perform well. The different lengths come in handy for different uses. The only problem I had is I used one of these in my Truck with Apple Car Play. We live in Wisconsin where in the winter, we get a lot of snow and they put a lot of salt on the roads. The end of the cable fell into that slushy mix once when I got out of my truck and disconnected my phone. After being exposed to that salty snow mix, the connector corroded rendering the cable useless. Cleaning the connector proved futile. Other than susceptibility to easy corrosion, they perform well. Piece of advice, pay attention to the environment that you are using them in as they are not as durable as they could be. There are contact platings that would reduce this problem, but that would add to the cost.
